A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. “There are so many anecdotes of people saying they are still with the bank that was across the road from their first job,” Chief Executive Officer Hylton Kallner said in an interview. “While that branch might not exist any longer they are still with the bank because it was too much of a hassle to change.” South Africans are gradually becoming more discerning as their options grow beyond the four big lenders that traditionally dominated the market. In 2015, the country’s Registrar of Banks received its first application for a new license in 11 years from TymeBank, a venture backed by billionaire Patrice Motsepe. Several digital challengers have since launched including Discovery, which now has more than 300 000 clients.